messages.content: Her: I like your smile.
Me: I like you.
Her: You remind me of someone.
Me: Who? The pretty girl I'm taking out next week?
Her: That was actually clever.
Me: Creativity inevitably leads to attraction.
Her: So that's your creative talent? Pickup lines?
Me: You call it pickup lines. I call it modern poetry.
Her: Romeo definitely didn’t say that.
Me: He should have. No wonder he got dumped.
Her: They both die in the end.
Me: Sounds like a skill issue.
Her: So you’re a writer?
Me: No, I’m the plot twist.
Her: I don’t give my number to strangers.
Me: Lucky for you, we’re about to change that status.
Her: What if I’m already talking to someone?
Me: There’s a reason you said ‘talking’ and not ‘taken’.
Her: No promises though.
Me: Promises are for the hesitant. You seem pretty sure to me.
Her: What is illegal?
Me: Clicking pictures of artwork in the museum.
Her: That's a bold statement.
Me: I'm a bold guy.
Her: Not sure if you can match my fun side.
Me: The only thing you shouldn't be sure of is how you'll stop yourself from getting addicted to all the fun we have.
Her: I appreciate your confidence
Me: I appreciate you hiding your eyes in that picture.
Her: why??
Me: Artworks can be revealed, the artist shouldn't.
Her: What?? My eyes aren't the artist
Me: There's a reason the eyes are called the window into the soul.
Her: You definitely do this often
Me: I've met a few artworks in the journey.
Her: So how do I know I'm just not another artwork?
Me: You don't, I do.
Her: How?
Me: This time I'm more interested in the artist than the artwork.
Her: I'm speechless sir
Me: Well, get that fixed ‘cause I wanna hear your voice. Drop your number.
Her: What did you want to say?
Me: You are definetely an only child.
Her: You love making assumptions, don't you? and no, I'm not.
Me: You're acting like one
Her: What do you mean?
Me: Why don't I tell you after you give me your number?
Her: I don't even know you sir
Me: Don't worry, you'll want to.
Her: Cocky much??
Me: I know, I'm one of god's favourite.
Her: Seems like you do this often.
Me: Do what?
Her: Slide into dms, and talk to a lot of girls
Me: Only to the one who earns it.
Her: So does it mean I've earned it?
Me: I like your chances
Her: You are very cocky, is that confidence or arrogance?
Me: Let's just focus on what matters.
Her: and whats that?
Me: That you like it
Her: That was good
Me: I have other good things to tell you, drop that number :))
Her: what did you want to say?
Me: So the rumours are true.
Her: What rumours?
Me: That we are going on a date.
Her: I want some of what you're smoking
Me: That's a trade secret, I'll tell you after you give me your number.
Her: Not gonna happen.
Me: I Hope you don't gamble
Her: There's a fine line between confidence and overconfidence.
Me: And very few have the confidence to cross it.
Her: You are either using AI, or you do this often.
Me: You could have just said that you're loving it
Her: Your opening was creative, I'll give you that.
Me: All thanks to my overconfidence.
Her: That was definetely different lol.
Me: You know what else is different?
Her: You?
Me: This story that we are living rn.
Her: I agree haha
Me: Let's write the next chapter.
Her: and what is that?
Me: We take the conversation to a more personal level
Her: How, you're going to ask me something personal?
Me: Let's start with taking this conversation over to texts, drop your number.
Her: what do you want?
Me: You look like my next girlfriend.
Her: I'm not available boy, but I appreciate the effort.
Me: I'm good at making offers people can't refuse.
Her: So you think I can do better?
Me: I don't think it, I know it.
Her: The confidence is crazy T.T
Me: You don't know the half of it.
Her: Be honest, do you do this with every girl?
Me: Only with the pretty ones.
Her: I like the confidence. I'm interested in the reason behind it.
Me: I could tell you, but I'd rather show.
Her: You are good at this.
Me: Tell me something I don't know.
Her: You don't know a lot mister.
Me: I love learning about beautiful things and their phone number.
Her: You move quick, don't you.
Me: I love fast cars for a reason, let's move this over to instagram not tinder.
Her: you have a compliment for me?
Me: Your beauty is one thing money can't buy.
Her: It depends on the offer dear.
Me: No it depends on who's selling and that's one reason I am here.
Her: Well name one thing I can't resist then we'll see if you're worthwhile
Me: Paying attention, and the second reason is because I see potential in you.
Her: That's your highest bid? Tell me what do you do for a girl on a first date.
Me: Firstly, I don't date just a girl. I date a lady. And a lady knows not to speak about a first date because it's better of a surprise am I right?
Her: Well, the men I know have more to offer unfortunately. Don't take it to heart.

Me: And why would I take anything you do to heart when you haven't owned it yet sweetheart. I'm wise enough to know that other men don't have the luxury to talk to you right now expect me. So whatever they offered did not keep the llady interested.
Her: Well, my time is expensive.
Me: Attention is the highest currency and I'm willing to spend it on you sweetheart
Her: I'd rather have you take me to a dinner instead...I know a restaurant that actually might tickle your fancy. Let me take you there... it's on me.
Me: No, I'll take it from there. The only place I want you to take me is your heart. anything else I'll take the lead.

Her: Ok mister, you are so uptight haha. Can't wait though. Just text you on my alternate account. Also second date is on me. If it goes well ,don't be surprised if I challenge you yeah? because it turns me on *lipbite emoji*
Me: I like where this is going.
Her: What did you want to talk about?
Me: I had a dream about this exact moment.
Her: Do you remember how the dream ended?
Me: Vivid enough to know it was a long time wish for the both of us.
Her: Do you mind telling me about this dream of yours.
Me: I would but actions speak louder than words so I'd rather show you.
Her: What If I have a dream about someone else?
Me: Once I show you my dream I assure you your dream about someone would be a nightmare.
Her: This 'dream' sounds like an obsession
Me: It does involve obsession
Her: I think I'm getting a glimpse of the "dream" but I know what obsession does when a male and female are involved so I suggest it stops here.
Me: If you know what obsession does then you definetely know it doesn't stop here.
Her: Does this dream have a starting or an ending?
Me: It doesn't have both.
Her: You didn't have a dream then am I right?
Me: Not yet but I know it belongs to me. The dream has no start and no ending because you are the dream. and thats why dreaming about others would be a nightmare.
Her: I've never met a guy like this.
Me: Let's change that, slide your phone number.
